stnAtm.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

VcLinkOperStatus.name: VcLinkOperStatus
VcLinkOperStatus.description: Operational status of a VC Link.

VcCrossConnOperStatus.name: VcCrossConnOperStatus
VcCrossConnOperStatus.description: Operational status of a VC cross connection.

TrafficDescrOperStatus.name: TrafficDescrOperStatus
TrafficDescrOperStatus.description: Operational status of a traffic descriptor.

AtmPortOperStatus.name: AtmPortOperStatus
AtmPortOperStatus.description: Operational status of an ATM port.

stnVcLinkTable.name: stnVcLinkTable
stnVcLinkTable.description: A list of VC Link entries.

stnVcLinkEntry.name: stnVcLinkEntry
stnVcLinkEntry.description: Entry contains information about a particular VC link.

stnVcLinkIfIndex.name: stnVcLinkIfIndex
stnVcLinkIfIndex.description: The interface index represents a connection point on the switch fabric from a module or line card. It is calculated based on the slot and port of the module.

stnVcLinkVpi.name: stnVcLinkVpi
stnVcLinkVpi.description: The VPI value of the VPL. Note that the VPI=0 is not used for a VPL not associated with a VCL. The maximum VPI value cannot exceed the value allowable by the atmInterfaceMaxVpiBits.

stnVcLinkVci.name: stnVcLinkVci
stnVcLinkVci.description: The VCI value of the VCL. The maximum VCI value cannot exceed the value allowable by the atmInterfaceMaxVciBits.

stnVcLinkRcvTrafDescr.name: stnVcLinkRcvTrafDescr
stnVcLinkRcvTrafDescr.description: Receive traffic descriptor identifier for this VPL.

stnVcLinkXmtTrafDescr.name: stnVcLinkXmtTrafDescr
stnVcLinkXmtTrafDescr.description: Transmit traffic descriptor identifier for this VPL.

stnVcLinkAalObjectsValid.name: stnVcLinkAalObjectsValid
stnVcLinkAalObjectsValid.description: Indicates whether the following AAL objects are valid (whether the local VCL end-point is also the VCC end-point). Transmit traffic descriptor identifier for this VPL.

stnVcLinkAalType.name: stnVcLinkAalType
stnVcLinkAalType.description: An instance of this object only exists when the local VCL end-point is also the VCC end-point, and AAL is in use. The type of AAL used on this VCC. The AAL type includes AAL1, AAL3/4, and AAL5. The other(4) may be used as a user-defined AAL type. The unknown type indicates that the AAL type cannot be determined.

stnVcLinkAal5XmtSDUSize.name: stnVcLinkAal5XmtSDUSize
stnVcLinkAal5XmtSDUSize.description: An instance of this object only exists when the local VCL end-point is also the VCC end-point, and AAL5 is in use. The maximum AAL5 CPCS SDUsize in octets that is supported on the transmit direction of this VCC.

stnVcLinkAal5RcvSDUSize.name: stnVcLinkAal5RcvSDUSize
stnVcLinkAal5RcvSDUSize.description: An instance of this object only exists when the local VCL end-point is also the VCC end-point, and AAL5 is in use. The maximum AAL5 CPCS SDU size in octets that is supported on the receive direction of this VCC.

stnVcLinkAal5EncapsType.name: stnVcLinkAal5EncapsType
stnVcLinkAal5EncapsType.description: An instance of this object only exists when the local VCL end-point is also the VCC end-point, and AAL5 is in use. The type of data encapsulation used over the AAL5 SSCS layer. The definitions reference RFC 1483 Multiprotocol Encapsulation over ATM AAL5 and to the ATM Forum LAN Emulation specification.

stnVcLinkCastType.name: stnVcLinkCastType
stnVcLinkCastType.description: The type of topology of a connection (point- to-point, point-to-multipoint). In the case of point-to-multipoint, the orientation of this VPL in the connection. On a host, p2mpRoot indicates that the host is the root of the p2mp connection, p2mpLeaf indicates that the host is a leaf of the p2mp connection. On a switch, p2mpRoot indicates that cells received by the switching fabric from the interface are from the root of the p2mp connection, p2mpLeaf indicates that cells transmitted to the interface from the switching fabric are to the leaf of the p2mp connection.

stnVcLinkConnKind.name: stnVcLinkConnKind
stnVcLinkConnKind.description: The use of call control. An spvcInitiator is always cross-connected to an svcOutgoing, and an spvcTarget is always cross-connected to an svcIncoming.

stnVcLinkAccEnabled.name: stnVcLinkAccEnabled
stnVcLinkAccEnabled.description: ATM accounting is enabled for this VC Link.

stnVcLinkOAMXmtFrequency.name: stnVcLinkOAMXmtFrequency
stnVcLinkOAMXmtFrequency.description: Number of seconds between transmitting OAM loopback cells.

stnVcLinkOAMRetryUpCount.name: stnVcLinkOAMRetryUpCount
stnVcLinkOAMRetryUpCount.description: Number of consecutive end-to-end F5 OAM loopback cell responses that must be received in order to change a PVC state to up. Does not apply to SVCs.

stnVcLinkOAMRetryDownCount.name: stnVcLinkOAMRetryDownCount
stnVcLinkOAMRetryDownCount.description: Number of consecutive end-to-end F5 OAM loopback cell responses that are not received in order to change a PVC state to down or tear down an SVC.

stnVcLinkOAMRetryFrequency.name: stnVcLinkOAMRetryFrequency
stnVcLinkOAMRetryFrequency.description: The frequency (in seconds) that end-to-end F5 loopback cells should be transmitted when a change in UP/DOWN state is being verified. For example, if a PVC is up and a loopback cell response is not received after the frequency (in seconds, then loopback cells are sent at the retry-frequency to verify whether or not the PVC is down.

stnVcLinkOperStatus.name: stnVcLinkOperStatus
stnVcLinkOperStatus.description: Operational status of the VC Link.

stnVcCrossConnTable.name: stnVcCrossConnTable
stnVcCrossConnTable.description: A list of VC cross connection entries.

stnVcCrossConnEntry.name: stnVcCrossConnEntry
stnVcCrossConnEntry.description: Entry contains information about a particular VC cross connection.

stnVcCrossConnLowIfIndex.name: stnVcCrossConnLowIfIndex
stnVcCrossConnLowIfIndex.description: The value of this object is equal to MIB II's ifIndex value of the ATM interface port for this VP cross-connect. The term low implies that this ATM interface has the numerically lower ifIndex.

stnVcCrossConnLowVpi.name: stnVcCrossConnLowVpi
stnVcCrossConnLowVpi.description: The value of this object is equal to the VPI value at the ATM interface associated with the VP cross-connect that is identified by LowIfIndex. The VPI value cannot exceed the number supported by the atmInterfaceMaxVpiBits at the low ATM interface port.

stnVcCrossConnLowVci.name: stnVcCrossConnLowVci
stnVcCrossConnLowVci.description: The value of this object is equal to the VCI value at the ATM interface associated with the VC cross-connect that is identified by LowIfIndex. The VCI value cannot exceed the number supported by the atmInterfaceMaxVciBits at the low ATM interface port.

stnVcCrossConnHighIfIndex.name: stnVcCrossConnHighIfIndex
stnVcCrossConnHighIfIndex.description: The value of this object is equal to MIB II's ifIndex value of the ATM interface port for this VP cross-connect. The term low implies that this ATM interface has the numerically lower ifIndex.

stnVcCrossConnHighVpi.name: stnVcCrossConnHighVpi
stnVcCrossConnHighVpi.description: The value of this object is equal to the VPI value at the ATM interface associated with the VP cross-connect that is identified by LowIfIndex. The VPI value cannot exceed the number supported by the atmInterfaceMaxVpiBits at the low ATM interface port.

stnVcCrossConnHighVci.name: stnVcCrossConnHighVci
stnVcCrossConnHighVci.description: The value of this object is equal to the VCI value at the ATM interface associated with the VC cross-connect that is identified by LowIfIndex. The VCI value cannot exceed the number supported by the atmInterfaceMaxVciBits at the low ATM interface port.

stnVcCrossConnLowAutoAssign.name: stnVcCrossConnLowAutoAssign
stnVcCrossConnLowAutoAssign.description: Controls low vpi/vci/ifIndex auto assignement to an ECF. If set to true MSM will attempt to dynamically auto assign the connection to an available ECF.

stnVcCrossConnHighAutoAssign.name: stnVcCrossConnHighAutoAssign
stnVcCrossConnHighAutoAssign.description: Controls high vpi/vci/ifIndex auto assignement to an ECF. If set to true MSM will attempt to dynamically auto assign the connection to an available ECF.

stnVcCrossConnOperStatus.name: stnVcCrossConnOperStatus
stnVcCrossConnOperStatus.description: Operational status of the VC cross connection.

stnTrafficDescrTable.name: stnTrafficDescrTable
stnTrafficDescrTable.description: A list of ATM traffic descriptor entries.

stnTrafficDescrEntry.name: stnTrafficDescrEntry
stnTrafficDescrEntry.description: Entry contains information about a particular ATM traffic descriptor.

stnTrafDescrIndex.name: stnTrafDescrIndex
stnTrafDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the stnTrafficDescrTable.

stnTrafDescrName.name: stnTrafDescrName
stnTrafDescrName.description: Text name assigned to this traffic descriptor.

stnTrafDescrType.name: stnTrafDescrType
stnTrafDescrType.description: The value of this object identifies the type of ATM traffic descriptor. The type may indicate no traffic descriptor or traffic descriptor with one or more parameters. These parameters are specified as a parameter vector, in the corresponding instances of the objects: atmTrafDescrParam1, atmTrafDescrParam2, atmTrafDescrParam3, atmTrafDescrParam4, atmTrafDescrParam5 Type values are as follows: no-td no-clp-no-scr clp-no-ag-no-scr clp-agging-no-scr no-clp-scr clp-no-tag-scr clp-tagging-scr clp-no-tag-mcr clp-trans-no-scr clp-trans-scr no-clp-tag-no-scr

stnTrafDescrParam1.name: stnTrafDescrParam1
stnTrafDescrParam1.description: The first parameter of the ATM traffic descriptor used according to the value of atmTrafDescrType.

stnTrafDescrParam2.name: stnTrafDescrParam2
stnTrafDescrParam2.description: The second parameter of the ATM traffic descriptor used according to the value of atmTrafDescrType.

stnTrafDescrParam3.name: stnTrafDescrParam3
stnTrafDescrParam3.description: The third parameter of the ATM traffic descriptor used according to the value of atmTrafDescrType.

stnTrafDescrParam4.name: stnTrafDescrParam4
stnTrafDescrParam4.description: The fourth parameter of the ATM traffic descriptor used according to the value of atmTrafDescrType.

stnTrafDescrParam5.name: stnTrafDescrParam5
stnTrafDescrParam5.description: The fifth parameter of the ATM traffic descriptor used according to the value of atmTrafDescrType.

stnTrafDescrQosClass.name: stnTrafDescrQosClass
stnTrafDescrQosClass.description: The value of this object identifies the QoS Class. Four Service classes have been specified in the ATM Forum UNI Specification: Service Class A: Constant bit rate video and Circuit emulation. Service Class B: Variable bit rate video/audio. Service Class C: Connection-oriented data. Service Class D: Connectionless data. Four QoS classes numbered 1, 2, 3, and 4 have been specified with the aim to support service classes A, B, C, and D respectively. An unspecified QoS Class numbered '0' is used for best effort traffic.

stnTrafDescrServiceCategory.name: stnTrafDescrServiceCategory
stnTrafDescrServiceCategory.description: The ATM service category. Service categories are as follows: other, cbr, rt-vbr, nrt-vbr, abr, ubr

stnTrafDescrFrameDiscard.name: stnTrafDescrFrameDiscard
stnTrafDescrFrameDiscard.description: Whether the network should discard frames rather than cells.

stnTrafDescrOperStatus.name: stnTrafDescrOperStatus
stnTrafDescrOperStatus.description: Operational status of the traffic descriptor.

stnTrafDescrCommittedRate.name: stnTrafDescrCommittedRate
stnTrafDescrCommittedRate.description: The traffic rate in bits per second that the network is committed to transmit for VCs using this transmit traffic descriptor.

stnTrafDescrMaximumRate.name: stnTrafDescrMaximumRate
stnTrafDescrMaximumRate.description: The maximum traffic rate in bits per second that the network will transmit for VCs using this transmit traffic descriptor, if it differs from the committed rate.

stnTraceIpsEnabled.name: stnTraceIpsEnabled
stnTraceIpsEnabled.description: Specifies whether IPS tracing is enabled.

stnTraceIpsSize.name: stnTraceIpsSize
stnTraceIpsSize.description: Specifies the maximum IPS trace buffer size multipled by 1024. The IPS trace log file will wrap when it reaches the maximum. Default: 1000 x 1024 Lines

stnTraceIpsFile.name: stnTraceIpsFile
stnTraceIpsFile.description: Specifies the IPS output path and file name. Changes to the path or filename take effect when IPS tracing is disabled and restarted (close file and open new).

stnTracePdProblemEnabled.name: stnTracePdProblemEnabled
stnTracePdProblemEnabled.description: Specifies whether PD problem tracing is enabled.

stnTracePdExceptionEnabled.name: stnTracePdExceptionEnabled
stnTracePdExceptionEnabled.description: Specifies whether PD exception tracing is enabled.

stnTracePdAuditEnabled.name: stnTracePdAuditEnabled
stnTracePdAuditEnabled.description: Specifies whether PD audit tracing is enabled.

stnTracePdDeveloperEnabled.name: stnTracePdDeveloperEnabled
stnTracePdDeveloperEnabled.description: Specifies whether PD developer tracing is enabled.

stnTracePdSize.name: stnTracePdSize
stnTracePdSize.description: Specifies the maximum PD trace buffer size multipled by 1024. The PD trace log file will wrap when it reaches the maximum.

stnTracePdFile.name: stnTracePdFile
stnTracePdFile.description: Specifies the IPS output path and file name. Changes to the path or filename take effect when IPS tracing is disabled and restarted.

stnAtmPortAttrTable.name: stnAtmPortAttrTable
stnAtmPortAttrTable.description: A list of ATM port attribute entries.

stnAtmPortAttrEntry.name: stnAtmPortAttrEntry
stnAtmPortAttrEntry.description: Entry contains information about a particular ATM port attribute entry.

stnAtmPortIfIndex.name: stnAtmPortIfIndex
stnAtmPortIfIndex.description: The interface index represents a connection point on the switch fabric from a module or line card. It is calculated based on the slot and port of the module.

stnAtmPortIfType.name: stnAtmPortIfType
stnAtmPortIfType.description: The interface type of the connection point to the switch fabric. Values are: sonet(1), enet(2), epif(3), rim-enet(4).

stnAtmPortIfState.name: stnAtmPortIfState
stnAtmPortIfState.description: The interface state of the connection point to the switch fabric. Values are: not-present(0), detected(1), configured(2), up-non-redundant(3), up-redundant(4), down-non-redundant(5), down-redundant(6), failed(7), initialized(8)

stnAtmPortEnabled.name: stnAtmPortEnabled
stnAtmPortEnabled.description: Whether the ATM port is enabled.

stnAtmPortMinVccVpi.name: stnAtmPortMinVccVpi
stnAtmPortMinVccVpi.description: Minimum VPI used for Virtual Channel Circuits.

stnAtmPortMaxVccVpi.name: stnAtmPortMaxVccVpi
stnAtmPortMaxVccVpi.description: Maximum VPI used for Virtual Channel Circuits.

stnAtmPortMinVccVci.name: stnAtmPortMinVccVci
stnAtmPortMinVccVci.description: Minimum VCI used for Virtual Channel Circuits. To avoid clashes with the reserved ATM VCI values (such as 5 for signaling and any other reserved values including Connection Manager VCs), the recommended value is 32.

stnAtmPortMaxVccVci.name: stnAtmPortMaxVccVci
stnAtmPortMaxVccVci.description: Maximum VCI used for Virtual Channel Circuits.

stnAtmPortMinVpcVpi.name: stnAtmPortMinVpcVpi
stnAtmPortMinVpcVpi.description: Minimum VPI used for Virtual Path Circuits. To avoid clashes with the reserved ATM VCCs values (such as 5 for signaling and any other reserved values including Connection Manager VCs), the recommended value is 1.

stnAtmPortMaxVpcVpi.name: stnAtmPortMaxVpcVpi
stnAtmPortMaxVpcVpi.description: Maximum VCI used for Virtual Channel Circuits.

stnAtmPortMaxActivePaths.name: stnAtmPortMaxActivePaths
stnAtmPortMaxActivePaths.description: The maximum number of active paths that can be active at any time on this port.

stnAtmPortMaxActiveChannels.name: stnAtmPortMaxActiveChannels
stnAtmPortMaxActiveChannels.description: The maximum number of virtual channels that can be active at any time on this port.

stnAtmPortPVCAddress.name: stnAtmPortPVCAddress
stnAtmPortPVCAddress.description: The default configured PVC address information (20-byte NSAP address).

stnAtmPortSVCAddress.name: stnAtmPortSVCAddress
stnAtmPortSVCAddress.description: The default configured SVC address information (20-byte NSAP address).

stnAtmPortSigVpi.name: stnAtmPortSigVpi
stnAtmPortSigVpi.description: The VPI used for the signaling channel.

stnAtmPortSigVci.name: stnAtmPortSigVci
stnAtmPortSigVci.description: The VCI used for the signaling channel.

stnAtmPortSigEnabled.name: stnAtmPortSigEnabled
stnAtmPortSigEnabled.description: Indicates if port will have a signaling stack.

stnAtmPortIlmiVpi.name: stnAtmPortIlmiVpi
stnAtmPortIlmiVpi.description: The VPI used for ILMI channel.

stnAtmPortIlmiVci.name: stnAtmPortIlmiVci
stnAtmPortIlmiVci.description: The VCI used for ILMI channel.

stnAtmPortIlmiEnabled.name: stnAtmPortIlmiEnabled
stnAtmPortIlmiEnabled.description: Indicates if port will use ILMI.

stnAtmPortOamManagementEnabled.name: stnAtmPortOamManagementEnabled
stnAtmPortOamManagementEnabled.description: Indicates if port is using OAM Management Procedures.

stnAtmPortOamXmtFrequency.name: stnAtmPortOamXmtFrequency
stnAtmPortOamXmtFrequency.description: Indicates Frequency of OAM Transmit Cells.

stnAtmPortOamRetryUpCount.name: stnAtmPortOamRetryUpCount
stnAtmPortOamRetryUpCount.description: Indicates OAM Cell Retry Up Count value.

stnAtmPortOamRetryDownCount.name: stnAtmPortOamRetryDownCount
stnAtmPortOamRetryDownCount.description: Indicates OAM Cell Retry Down Count value.

stnAtmPortIlmiTable.name: stnAtmPortIlmiTable
stnAtmPortIlmiTable.description: A list of ATM ILMI Port entries.

stnAtmPortIlmiEntry.name: stnAtmPortIlmiEntry
stnAtmPortIlmiEntry.description: Entry contains information about a particular ATM Port ILMI entry.

stnAtmPortIlmiIfIndex.name: stnAtmPortIlmiIfIndex
stnAtmPortIlmiIfIndex.description: The interface index represents a connection point on the switch fabric from a module or line card. It is calculated based on the slot and port of the module.

stnAtmPortIlmiVersion.name: stnAtmPortIlmiVersion
stnAtmPortIlmiVersion.description: Specifies the signaling stack protocol type to be used on this port. Valid options are: uni-3-dot-0 uni-3-dot-1 uni-4-dot-0 iisp-3-dot-1

stnAtmPortIlmiNetworkOrientation.name: stnAtmPortIlmiNetworkOrientation
stnAtmPortIlmiNetworkOrientation.description: Specifies the ATM device type. Valid options are: user, network

stnAtmPortIlmiPollInterval.name: stnAtmPortIlmiPollInterval
stnAtmPortIlmiPollInterval.description: ILMI connection poll interval (S) in seconds. When DC-ILMI is transmitting SNMP Get messages during the attempt to establish connectivity with the remote ILMI component, this parameter determines the time in seconds between transmissions. The default value is from the ATM Forum ILMI Specification Version 4.0: ILMI Connectivity Procedures (section 8.3.1).

stnAtmPortIlmiCheckConnectionInt.name: stnAtmPortIlmiCheckConnectionInt
stnAtmPortIlmiCheckConnectionInt.description: ILMI check connection poll interval (T) in seconds. If connectivity checking is enabled (as spec by the value connect in the Admin_Status parameter below), this parameter specifies the time in seconds between successive transmissions of MIB Get msgs for the purpose of detecting loss of ILMI connectivity. If connectivity checking is not enabled, this parameter must be set to zero. The default value is from the ATM Forum ILMI Specification Version 4.0: ILMI Connectivity Procedures (section 8.3.1).

stnAtmPortIlmiInactivityFactor.name: stnAtmPortIlmiInactivityFactor
stnAtmPortIlmiInactivityFactor.description: ILMI inactivity factor (K). The number of consecutive polls for which no response is received from the remote ILMI component before ILMI connectivity is assumed to be lost. The dflt value is from the ATM Forum ILMI Specification Version 4.0: ILMI Connectivity Procedures (section 8.3.1).

stnAtmPortIlmiLocalConn.name: stnAtmPortIlmiLocalConn
stnAtmPortIlmiLocalConn.description: Specifies whether the local end of the ILMI connection is advertised as a 'public' or 'private' ILMI device. Values are: other, public, private

stnAtmPortIlmiAdminStatus.name: stnAtmPortIlmiAdminStatus
stnAtmPortIlmiAdminStatus.description: Specifies which functions of DC-ILMI are enabled. The value std-ilmi must be specified; this value may be combined (using a bitwise OR) with one or more of the following values: std-ilmi - Standard ILMI functions are enabled. addr-reg - Address registration is enabled. connect - Connectivity chcking is enabled (DC-ILMI periodically sends a MIB Get request for the remote system's System ID, to ensure that it can still send and rcvd data on the ILMI connection). Default: (std-ilmi | addr-reg | connect)

stnAtmPortIlmiEnterprise.name: stnAtmPortIlmiEnterprise
stnAtmPortIlmiEnterprise.description: Enterprise Object ID that DC-ILMI will use in building SNMP traps (or other generic MIB traps). This parameter can be used to identify the originator of the trap. The Object ID is specified as an array of unsigned long vals, as follows: The first entry in the array is the length of the array (the num of unsigned long values it contains, including the len value). The second entry in the array is an identifier specifying the Family type of the Object ID. This reps a prefix Object ID; the MIB Sub-Agent is responsible for matching this id with the dotted-decimal notation for this prefix. The remainder of the array gives the index part of the Object ID (the dotted-decimal notation from the end of the Family), with 1 unsigned long for each decimal number in this notation.

stnAtmPortIlmiLocalOid.name: stnAtmPortIlmiLocalOid
stnAtmPortIlmiLocalOid.description: Object ID identifying the local machine - the first 4 octets indicate the length of the object id. For example, the null object id (0.0), which should be used if no object id is specified, is encoded as 3, 0, 0.

stnAtmPortIlmiNetPrefix.name: stnAtmPortIlmiNetPrefix
stnAtmPortIlmiNetPrefix.description: Default network prefix. If the prefix length is non-zero, ILMI creates an entry in the ILMI NetPrefix Table for this prefix; otherwise the Net_Prefix parameter is not used.

stnAtmPortIlmiPrefixLen.name: stnAtmPortIlmiPrefixLen
stnAtmPortIlmiPrefixLen.description: The length of the default network prefix

stnAtmPortSigTable.name: stnAtmPortSigTable
stnAtmPortSigTable.description: A list of ATM port signal entries.

stnAtmPortSigEntry.name: stnAtmPortSigEntry
stnAtmPortSigEntry.description: Entry contains information about a particular ATM port signal entry.

stnAtmPortSigIfIndex.name: stnAtmPortSigIfIndex
stnAtmPortSigIfIndex.description: The interface index represents a connection point on the switch fabric from a module or line card. It is calculated based on the slot and port of the module.

stnAtmPortSigVersion.name: stnAtmPortSigVersion
stnAtmPortSigVersion.description: Specifies the signaling stack protocol type to be used on this port. Valid options are: UNI 3.0, UNI 3.1, IISP 3.1, PNNI 1.0

stnAtmPortSigNetworkOrientation.name: stnAtmPortSigNetworkOrientation
stnAtmPortSigNetworkOrientation.description: Indicates whether the ATM device is of the user or network type. Valid values are: user, network

stnAtmPortSigAssignVpiVci.name: stnAtmPortSigAssignVpiVci
stnAtmPortSigAssignVpiVci.description: Specifies whether VPI/VCI assignment is the responsibility of the local signaling stack or of its partner stack. This parameter is used only for UNI 4.0. Values are: true - The local signaling stack is responsible for assigning VPIs/VCIs. false - The parent-signaling stack is responsible for assigning VPIs/VCIs.

stnAtmPortSigVpSigType.name: stnAtmPortSigVpSigType
stnAtmPortSigVpSigType.description: Specifies whether this signaling stack performs VP associated signaling: Valid options are: associated-signaling explicit-vpci

stnAtmPortSigParseMode.name: stnAtmPortSigParseMode
stnAtmPortSigParseMode.description: Specifies whether the message parser component of Sig should perform validity checking on the contents of received IEs. This element resides in the CCS MIB to allow software config of this behavior for compliance testing. Values are: normal - The parser checks the contents of the IEs the Sig uses and ensures that they are valid. For other IEs, it checks only the IE type and length and does not parse the contents. strict - The parser checks the contents of addit IEs as well as those used by Signaling and also checks for incorrect repetition of these add it IEs. Errors are handled in the same way as for the IEs used by sig (by sending a status message in UNI 3.1 or by following the IE instruction indicator in UNI 4.0).

stnAtmPortSigPrefCarrierPresent.name: stnAtmPortSigPrefCarrierPresent
stnAtmPortSigPrefCarrierPresent.description: Specifies whether a default prefrd carrier (transit network) is defined. Valid options are: true - the Default_Network_Id below defines which carr is the preferred carrier. false - no default preferred carrier is defined.

stnAtmPortSigPrefCarrier.name: stnAtmPortSigPrefCarrier
stnAtmPortSigPrefCarrier.description: Specifies the default preferred carrier. If stnAtmPortIlmiPrefCarrierPresent is set to false, this element is not used.

stnAtmPortSigDurationTable.name: stnAtmPortSigDurationTable
stnAtmPortSigDurationTable.description: A list of ATM Port Signaling Duration entries.

stnAtmPortSigDurationEntry.name: stnAtmPortSigDurationEntry
stnAtmPortSigDurationEntry.description: Entry contains information about a particular ATM Port Signaling Duration entry.

stnAtmPortSigDurIfIndex.name: stnAtmPortSigDurIfIndex
stnAtmPortSigDurIfIndex.description: The interface index represents a connection point on the switch fabric from a module or line card. It is calculated based on the slot and port of the module.

stnAtmPortSigT301Duration.name: stnAtmPortSigT301Duration
stnAtmPortSigT301Duration.description: T301 timer. See ITU-T Q.2931 B-ISDN DSS2 User-Network Interface (UNI) Layer 3 Specification for Basic Call/Connection Control

stnAtmPortSigT303Duration.name: stnAtmPortSigT303Duration
stnAtmPortSigT303Duration.description: T303 timer. See ITU-T Q.2931 B-ISDN DSS2 User-Network Interface (UNI) Layer 3 Specification for Basic Call/Connection Control

stnAtmPortSigT306Duration.name: stnAtmPortSigT306Duration
stnAtmPortSigT306Duration.description: T306 timer. See ITU-T Q.2931 B-ISDN DSS2 User-Network Interface (UNI) Layer 3 Specification for Basic Call/Connection Control

stnAtmPortSigT308Duration.name: stnAtmPortSigT308Duration
